A //derivation// $$D$$ on an [[algebra|Algebra (algebraische Struktur)]] $$A$$ is an endomorphism which additionally satisfies the Leibniz-like rule
$$
D(ab) = D(a) b + a D(b).
$$
The term is also used for maps $$D \in A^*$$ satisfying the above rule.